snippet.title: God Gave Me A Girlfriend (Barron Trump Singing About His Girlfriend Imagined)
snippet.description:
God Gave Me A Girlfriend

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
Verse 1:
I prayed for love, I asked for grace,
For someone real, for someone safe.
Through all the noise, through all the lies,
God heard my prayer and opened my eyes.

Chorus:
God gave me a girlfriend, strong and true,
A heart of faith, a love so new.
Hand in hand, we walk His way,
With every step, we kneel and pray.

Verse 2:
She lifts me up when times get tough,
Reminds me that God's love’s enough.
Through every trial, through every fight,
She holds my hand and walks in light.

Chorus:
God gave me a girlfriend, strong and true,
A heart of faith, a love so new.
Hand in hand, we walk His way,
With every step, we kneel and pray.

Bridge:
When the world gets dark, when the road feels long,
We turn to Him—He keeps us strong.
With faith as our foundation stone,
We know we’ll never walk alone.

Final Chorus:
God gave me a girlfriend, sent from above,
A partner in faith, a life to love.
Through every trial, through every storm,
With God between us, we stay warm.

Outro:
So every night, I bow my head,
Thanking Him for where we’re led.
God gave me a girlfriend, and now I see,
His perfect plan was meant for me.
